# Tamagotchi build-time configuration — user-local, copy to .env and edit.
#
# The Makefile -includes .env (when present) and translates each
# supported key into a -D<KEY>=<value> flag passed to arduino-cli for
# every compile, so the same knob applies to both the main firmware
# and the bring-up tests under firmware/tests/.
#
# Format: plain `KEY=value`, one per line. No quotes, no `export`. Lines
# starting with # are comments.

# Set to 1 if your OLED is mounted upside-down (e.g. the panel pins
# face the bottom in your case). Rotates the display 180° at compile
# time — applies to both the main firmware and `make test-oled`. No
# runtime cost. Default: 0 (the SDA/SCL pins face up).
ROTATED_DISPLAY=0
